        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 4:53PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 453 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Happy, or 15 miles south of Canyon, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of south central
Randall County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
